<subSubSection id="C3115DA56E7C407BFF485B8514B59FC7" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="279" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E7C407BFF485B8514B59FC7" blockId="17.[151,1437,1843,2012]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,151,1005]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="279" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7C4078FF485B85164C98AA" bold="true" box="[199,321,1951,1976]" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsal-fin rays VII-I, 10; pectoral-fin rays 20–22; total gill rakers 29–32; vertebrae 10 + 15; pyloric caeca 12–14; pored lateral-line scales 45–48 + 3–4; scales below lateral line 11; pungent opercular spine present; maxillary mustache-like processes absent; ribs on last abdominal vertebra absent or rarely reduced ribs present; nub-like structures on symphysis of lower jaw absent; tongue toothless.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3115DA56E7F407BFF485CC515CC9D2F" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E7F407BFF485CC515CC9D2F" blockId="18.[151,1436,151,1005]" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFF485CC516D19FEA" bold="true" box="[199,476,223,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">Measurements (% SL)</emphasis>
; counts are given in Table 1. Head length 36.2–39.1; head width 15.6–18.5; head height 13.1–16.7; body depth 19.1–23.0; body width 13.0–15.7; caudal-peduncle depth 8.6–9.7; caudal-peduncle length 23.8–25.6; orbital diameter 15.5–17.1; interorbital width 7.0–8.9; postorbital length 14.0–16.6; upper-jaw length 12.8–14.3; lower-jaw length 15.2–16.6; snout length 6.2–7.6; pre-first dorsal-fin length 36.8–38.8; presecond dorsal-fin length 59.0–62.2; pre-pectoral-fin length 35.4–38.4; pre-pelvic-fin length 36.2–38.8; pre-anus length 56.8–60.4; pre-anal-fin length 66.5–76.1; first spine length on first dorsal fin 2.0–3.1; second spine length on first dorsal fin 14.7–17.0; third spine length on first dorsal fin 15.2–19.0; second dorsal-fin spine length 8.0–9.6; first anal-fin spine length 2.2–3.3; second anal-fin spine length 8.1–11.1; pelvic-fin spine length 12.5–14.5; first dorsal-fin base length 11.5–14.0; second dorsal-fin base length 10.0–11.4; anal-fin base length 9.5–10.8; pectoralfin length 13.4–16.3; pelvic-fin length 16.0–18.8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3115DA56E7F407BFF485E5D13FB9CFF" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E7F407BFF485E5D16269D97" blockId="18.[151,1436,151,1005]" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFF485E5D166D9D72" bold="true" box="[199,352,583,608]" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">Distribution.</emphasis>
Arabian Sea; western 
<collectingRegion id="49CFC0CC6E7F407BFDEA5E5D15AA9D72" box="[613,679,583,608]" country="Tanzania" name="Kusini Unguja" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">South</collectingRegion>
Indian Ocean (Parin &amp; Abramov 1986a; Okamoto 2012), at 
<quantity id="4CF3A3CB6E7F407BFAEB5E5D17D39D96" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.075" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.95" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" unit="m" value="407.5" valueMax="420.0" valueMin="395.0">395– 420 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E7F407BFF485E9513FB9CFF" blockId="18.[151,1436,151,1005]" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFF485E9515139DBA" bold="true" box="[199,542,655,680]" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">Comparisons and Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFDA55E8A14429DBA" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[554,847,656,680]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFDA55E8A14429DBA" box="[554,847,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">Epigonus marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFB825E8B13BA9DB5" baseAuthorityName="Giglioli" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1037,1207,656,680]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="constanciae">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFB825E8B13BA9DB5" box="[1037,1207,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. constanciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by having a pungent opercular spine (
<figureCitation id="133012AB6E7F407BFE315EAE15199DDE" box="[446,532,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1541,1563]" captionTargetBox="[206,1398,1060,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[188,1398,1060,1520]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 14. Epigonus marimonticolus, LACM 44723-3, 1 of 6 specimens, 133.8 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182197/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFC145EAF133E9DDE" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[923,1075,692,716]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFC145EAF133E9DDE" box="[923,1075,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the study area; however, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFA0B5EAF164B9DE2" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFA0B5EAF164B9DE2" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFE555EC315639DE2" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[474,622,728,752]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFE555EC315639DE2" box="[474,622,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lacking spines on the symphysis of the lower jaw and a pair of ribs on the last abdominal vertebra (see 
<figureCitation id="133012AB6E7F407BFD8B5EE615469C07" box="[516,587,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1329,1351]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,511,1307]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,481,1307]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Lateral view (A) and radiograph (B) of Epigonus bispinosus n. sp., SAIAB 189476, holotype, 165.5 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182177/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">Figs 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133012AB6E7F407BFDD75EE615739C07" box="[600,638,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[226,1344,1400,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[226,1360,1400,1852]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE6. Ventral viewof symphysis of lowerjaw.A:Epigonus bispinosusn. sp., SAIAB35606, 1of 5 paratypes,141.7 mm SL; B: Epigonus idai n. sp., SAIAB 204434, paratype, 132.3 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182179/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">6A</figureCitation>
). Also, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFD5A5EE714A99C06" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[725,932,764,788]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFD5A5EE714A99C06" box="[725,932,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFBB75EE713899C06" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1080,1156,764,788]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFBB75EE713899C06" box="[1080,1156,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having 10 soft rays in the second dorsal fin; however, it differs in having 20–22 pectoral fin rays and lacking a pair of ribs on the last abdominal vertebra (vs. 18–19 pectoral fin rays and ribs present on the last abdominal vertebra in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFB655F5F123B9C4E" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1258,1334,836,860]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFB655F5F123B9C4E" box="[1258,1334,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<figureCitation id="133012AB6E7F407BFAFF5F5E17CA9C92" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1968,1990]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,697,1947]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[188,1398,697,1947]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Epigonus idai n. sp., SAIAB 82171, holotype, 136.8 mm SL; A: fresh specimen; B: preserved specimen; C: radiograph." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182191/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFF535F7216F39C92" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[220,510,872,896]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFF535F7216F39C92" box="[220,510,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">Epigonus marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the remaining 4 species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFB015F7312399C6D" baseAuthorityName="Giglioli" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1166,1332,872,896]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="constanciae">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFB015F7312399C6D" box="[1166,1332,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. constanciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of the 
<collectingRegion id="49CFC0CC6E7F407BFF4E5F9716119CB6" box="[193,284,909,932]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Western" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">Western</collectingRegion>
Indian Ocean in having 10 soft rays on the second dorsal fin and 12–14 pyloric caeca (vs. 9 soft rays and 5–10 pyloric caeca in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFE4D5FAB15369CDA" authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1962" box="[450,571,944,968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenimen">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFE4D5FAB15369CDA" box="[450,571,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. lenimen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFDC65FAB15DE9CDA" authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[585,723,944,968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFDC65FAB15DE9CDA" box="[585,723,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFD6D5FAB146C9CDA" baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[738,865,944,968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFD6D5FAB146C9CDA" box="[738,865,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFC2E5FAB13469CDA" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[929,1099,944,968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="waltersensis">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFC2E5FAB13469CDA" box="[929,1099,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. waltersensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In their ichthyofaunal study of the Arabian Sea, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A73DF6E7F407BFEF95FCE15C89CFE" box="[374,709,980,1005]" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" refId="ref20021" refString="Manilo, L. G. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V. (2003) Taxonomic composition, diversity and distribution of coastal fishes of the Arabian Sea. Journal of Ichthyology, 43 (Supplement), 75 - 149. [S 75 - S 149]" type="journal article">Manilo &amp; Bogorodsky (2003)</bibRefCitation>
listed only 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFCC75FCF131A9CFE" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[840,1047,980,1004]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7F407BFCC75FCF131A9CFE" box="[840,1047,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="279">E. marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7F407BFBE05FCE13FF9CFF" box="[1135,1266,980,1005]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="279" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Epigonidae</taxonomicName>
.
